<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=20 COLS=75 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Hi All!

About how agents can act I think a bit on "Chreatures". They have hunger, are angry and so on, and on a script based system. (I think you have that system already !?.)

What would be nice, is if the agents could learn fron the char.! If he often let mosters follow him, the monsters ´ll learn nor to follow him. If he everytime attacks without thinking, they ´ll make an anbush. So the char. has to change his way to act during the game. An other thing is that agents only react on things they know. (esacialy for NPCs) If a char. kills a man in the woods and nobódy sees this nobody is angry about him. (besides the good gods) But if would kill someone inside a town the people would hate him therefor. The same is it with good things. Why does the people like me if they don´t know how I´m? Some people like anventurers others hate them, even if they like good thinks (like the char.) too. The char. first must "get a name", bevore the people ´ll akt like he has one. So if he is the first time in a small town an everybody likes him, that doesn´t mean, that the people in big city, nearby know who he is. There he has to start again to impress them.
A other thin with NPCs is that they have some things they do every day. e.g. the baker goes each morning to his bakery (betreen 3.00 and 3.10). It would be nice if I could realy see him go to work an not only wait in front of the bakery up to the time it opens.
*ingame*
the char. waits in front of the door. 5 minutes bevore the bakery opens normaly the baker opens the door. `Cause he sees us in front of the door, he wishs us a wonderfull day and asks if we want something.
-&gt; Yes
He let us in and we come into the bying screen.
-&gt; No
He says bey and goes back into his bakery.
*end*

Monsters could act the same way.  e.g.:
one Ork has order to look for food. He wants to hunt a pig. (*Do you remember the story about this?  :) *) On his way he sees us.

-&gt; He is angry and runs away.

-&gt; He is inteligent and runs away and looks for others to hepl him.

-&gt; He strupid and atacks.

-&gt; He cries.

-&gt; a.s.o.
.


If the Char. would investigate a time he he would see the orks go to get food. Later he could make an ambush and arest one to get information out of him. (if he understands him.  :) ). If he would do this several times the orks would send one ork in front and would folow him with a big group. while the char. is in the the others would arrive and smach the char. at hte end. (if can´t run fast enought.  ;) )

That schould be diffrent posibilitys.

Risini Visinimi</TEXTAREA>
